                }, { "id": "CHI011E160",
                    "name": "IB Language and Literature 11 Y1",
                    "track": "IB",
                    "description": "This is a pre-university course designed for students with a high level of reading and writing competence in Chinese language. The emphasis of the course will be on the development of analytical skills in textual artistry as well as social and historical contexts through in-depth exploration of literary texts. Students will read both classic and modern Chinese literature and world literature in translation selected by the teacher according to the IB curriculum requirement. Written and spoken communication will be assessed through internal (school) and external (IBO) assessment. All students enrolled in an IB subject must sit the external exam at the end of Year2. This is a continuation of IB Chinese A: Literature Y1. The emphasis of the course will be on the development of analytical skills in literary artistry as well as social and historical contexts through in-depth exploration of literary texts. Students will read both classic and modern Chinese literature and world literature in translation selected by the teacher according to the IB curriculum requirement. Written and spoken communication will be assessed through internal (school) and external (IBO) assessment. All students enrolled in an IB subject must take the external exam at the end of Year2.",
