                    "description": "We begin with Greek philosophy through excerpts from Plato to give an historical understanding of linguistics before furthering our study of Shakespearean tragedy. Next we consider the role of satire in society and the subversive role of literature. We end the first half of the course with an introduction to narratology and the skills for intertextuality. In the second half of the course, we explore the themes and complexities of Modern and Postmodern literature. Students will also study voices of the world as they encounter literature from different places and cultures. Focus is on interpretation and analysis. Homework Expectation: 5-6 hours per week",
