                }, { "id": "ENG010F131",
                    "name": "English 10 H+",
                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "H+",
                    "description": "This course follows the content of Honors, but also aims to prepare students for the rigors of the Advanced Placement and International Baccalaureate programs through an in-depth exploration of world literature. Students will learn to utilize different critical approaches in the examination of rhetoric, poetry, drama, and prose, while simultaneously exploring larger conceptual frameworks for the understanding of their worlds. The evaluative battery for this course, closely aligned to the unique testing methodologies of the AP Language, AP Literature, and IB A English curricula, provides students with an opportunity to hone their skills in a supportive and lively classroom environment, while the unique blend of multimodal projects interspersed throughout the course encourages a sense of camaraderie and heightened creativity. Focus is on interpretation and analysis through theoretical lenses. Homework Expectation: 5-6 hours per week",
