                    "level": "H",
                    "description": "This advanced art course provides students with opportunities to continue the development of their art-making skills in order to express their own ideas, thoughts, and feelings through not just artwork and projects, but also research toward their work. There is a focus on creating artwork towards a portfolio while showing an understanding of the elements of art, principles of design, composition development, and an overview of the historical aspects of art. Students will be assessed on the research they keep in a sketchbook, art projects, class discussions and critiques, and tests that consist of vocabulary and critical thinking. This course also serves as preparation for IB or AP Art for the following year.",
                    "crowdRating": 0.0,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future."
                }, { "id": "ART110E170",
                    "name": "AP Drawing 10",
                    "track": "AP",
                    "description": "This is an advanced art course that challenges students to develop a portfolio consisting of breadth, quality, and a concentration. The breadth section will allow students to explore a variety of mediums, techniques, artistic approaches, and concepts to develop versatility with problem solving and abilities. A concentration will show a mastery of concept, composition, and execution of personal ideas and themes while also showing an understanding that art making is an ongoing process that uses informed and critical decision making to determine outcomes to problems. Artwork, critiques, and portfolio development will be assessed through internal (school) and external (AP Portfolio Review) assessments.",
                    "crowdRating": 0.0,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future."
                }
            ], "11": [
                {   "id": "ART111E150",
                    "name": "IB Visual Arts HL Y1",
                    "track": "IB",
                    "level": "HL",
                    "description": "The course requirements are based on the International Baccalaureate Art and Design curriculum, which emphasizes the use of a wide variety of media, research into various cultures, and personal thematic exploration. The goals for the first year are to acquaint the students with IB requirements (studio and Investigation Workbooks A4), help them determine a theme to pursue for the length of the program, expose them to a wide variety of media, and provide a general introduction to art history and movements. HL students are required to produce a larger body of work and work of greater depth.",
