                    "name": "Physical Geography 9 Honors",
                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "H",
                    "description": "This course introduces the physical characters of the earth, including climate issues, weather patterns, river processes, water usage, ocean processes, landforms, rocks, soils, etc. It examines formation of each geo-system, their operating mechanism, the interaction among different systems, impact of the physical environment upon people and the impact of people upon their physical environment. Students at this level will get to know far more than facts themselves. The acquisition of skills related to this course and its learning outcomes will be assessed through continuous evaluation including theoretical and practical tests, class participation as well as individual and group works.",
