                }, { "id": "HIS110E170",
                    "name": "AP World History 10",
                    "track": "AP",
                    "description": "The purpose of this course is to give students the skills and knowledge needed to excel at the AP World History test. The course is rigorous, and requires students to read an immense amount of background material so they can come to class prepared to discuss and further develop their historical thinking skills. Skills focused on in the class relate to looking at continuity and change over time and comparing different civilizations or aspects within them. The class starts and ends in the present day. Though the course runs for a full year, students need to take the exam in May, so they have approximately three semesters to get through all the material. Homework Expectation: 4-6 hours per week",
