                    "name": "Calculus 11 Standard",
                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "S",
                    "description": "Designed for students in Grade 11, this course aims to foster a fundamental understanding of calculus concepts and master the basic operations and applications. Topics covered in the course include limits, continuity, derivatives, definite integrals, and their applications . The course begins with a review of pre-calculus concepts, providing a gradual transition into the more advanced topics of calculus. This slower-paced approach makes the course more manageable, particularly for those students who may not encounter significant mathematical demands in their college and career paths.",
