                        "next": [["MAT012E93MC", "MAT012E50ST"]]
                    }
                }, { "id": "MAT011E71AA",
                    "name": "IB Mathematics: Analysis and Approaches SL Y1",
                    "track": "IB",
                    "level": "SL",
                    "description": "This course is intended for students who plan to pursue subjects with significant mathematical components, such as mathematics itself, engineering, physical sciences, or economics, among others. Given that mathematics is a sequential subject, it is required that students enrolling in the Diploma Program (DP) Mathematics: Analysis and Approaches SL course will have successfully completed AP Calculus or AP Pre-calculus in grade 10. This course reflects the emphasis on calculus and on algebraic, graphical and numerical approaches. It will develop students’ mathematics to become more fluent in the construction of mathematical arguments and develop strong skills in mathematical thinking. It will explore real and abstract applications with and without the use of technology. The aims of this course are to develop students’ abilities in communication, critical thinking, generalization, problem-solving, etc. There are 6 content sections, as listed below. Of them, sections 3 and 5 are the key sections. 1. Numbers and algebra; 2. Functions; 3. Trigonometry and geometry; 4. Statistics and probability; 5. Calculus; 6. “Toolkit” and IA. Students will take IB Mathematics: Analysis and Approaches SL Exam after the course.",
                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
