                    }
                }, { "id": "MAT011E71AI",
                    "name": "IB Mathematics: Applications and Interpretation SL Y1",
                    "track": "IB",
                    "level": "SL",
                    "description": "This course is intended for students who plan to pursue subjects such as social sciences, natural sciences, statistics, business, some economics, psychology, and design. Given that mathematics is a sequential subject, it is required that students enrolling in the Diploma Program (DP) Mathematics: applications and interpretation SL course will have successfully completed AP Calculus or AP Pre-calculus in grade 10, and possess strong English proficiency. This course emphasizes the applied nature of mathematics, and also that interpretation of results in context is an important element of this course. It will develop students’ mathematics for describing our world and solving practical problems. Students will harness the power of technology alongside exploring mathematical models. The aims of this course are to develop students’ abilities in communication, critical thinking, generalization, problem-solving, etc. There are 6 content sections, as listed below. And each section is a subset of Applications and Interpretation HL. 1. Numbers and algebra; 2. Functions; 3. Trigonometry and geometry; 4. Statistics and probability; 5. Calculus; 6. “Toolkit” and IA. Students will take IB Mathematics: Applications and Interpretation SL Exam after the course.",
                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future.",
                    "rules": {
