                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future.",
                    "rules": { "pre": [["MUS111E141"]] }
                }, { "id": "MUS112E170",
                    "name": "AP Music Theory 11",
                    "track": "AP",
                    "description": "The AP Music Theory course is an advanced course equivalent to first-year college music theory. It aims to serve students who are interested in studying or pursuing music performance, composition, or musicology at university or conservatory. The course is an introduction to tonal harmony from the Common Practice Period (1600-1900) of music history. The course is designed to connect theoretical music concepts with recognition and practical application skills in order to cultivate a competent musician. The AP Course intends to enhance students' knowledge of the aesthetic design that is crucial for understanding the music of the past and changes in theory that led to the developments of 20th century music. Objectives: Students will learn the systems used to analyze music at the micro and macro levels. In addition to studying musical scores, students will be expected to compose music and recreate common idioms as well as interpret music aurally (by ear). Upon completion of this course, students will have developed a set of practical musical skills as well as a more intuitive musical ear.",
