                    "rules": { "pre": [["PHY010E110"]], "next": [["PHY112E110"]] }
                }, { "id": "PHY111E130",
                    "name": "Physics 11 Honors",
                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "H",
                    "description": "This one year course is designed for the students who have a curiosity about the physical world but do not expect to major in engineering or the physical sciences. Emphasis is placed on covering the phenomena, concepts, and theories of modern physics such as rotation,thermal physics,and electromagnetism. Laboratory skills are developed. Students are expected to use scientific method to investigate, apply the ideas of physics to technology and develop an awareness of the impact of physics on society. In order to encourage the students to attend SAT II in physics upon completion 16SAT II.",
                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future.",
                    "rules": { "pre": [["PHY010E130"]], "next": [["PHY112E130"]] }
                }, { "id": "PHY111E170",
                    "name": "AP Physics 1 11",
                    "track": "AP",
                    "description": "AP Physics 1 is an algebra-based, introductory college-level physics course that explores topics such as Newtonian mechanics (including rotational motion); work, energy, and power; mechanical waves and sound; and introductory, simple circuits. Through inquiry-based learning, students will develop scientific critical thinking and reasoning skills. The curriculum framework is structured around the \u201cbig ideas\u201d, which encompass core scientific principles, theories, and processes of discipline. The framework encourages instruction that allows students to make connections across domains through a broader way of thinking about the physical world. Big ideas cut across the traditional principles of physics and are supported with enduring understandings, which communicate the core concepts that student should retain from their learning experiences. This course requires that 25 percent of the instructional time will be spent in hands-on laboratory work, with an emphasis on inquiry-based investigations that provide students with opportunities to apply the science practices.",
                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future.",
                    "rules": { "pre": [["PHY010E130"]], "current": [["MISSING: ENG 10S+"]], "next": [["PHY112E170"]] }
                }, { "id": "PHY111E140",
                    "name": "IB Physics SL Y1",
                    "track": "IB",
                    "level": "SL",
                    "description": "SL and HL undertake a common core syllabus, a common internal assessment scheme and have some overlapping elements in the option studied. They are presented with a syllabus that encourages the development of certain skills, attributes and attitudes. Students at HL are required to study some topics in greater depth, in addition to the higher level material and in the common option. The distinction between SL and HL is one of breadth and depth. Core: Measurements and uncertainties; Mechanics; Thermal physics; Waves; Electricity and magnetism; Circular motion and gravitation; Atomic, nuclear and particle physics; Energy production. Option: Imaging. Practical activities: 20 hours. Individual investigation: 10 hours. Group 4 project: 10 hours.",
                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future.",
                    "rules": { "pre": [["PHY010E130"]], "next": [["PHY112E140"]] }
                }, { "id": "PHY111E150",
                    "name": "IB Physics HL Y1",
                    "track": "IB",
                    "level": "HL",
                    "description": "SL and HL undertake a common core syllabus, a common internal assessment scheme and have some overlapping elements in the option studied. They are presented with a syllabus that encourages the development of certain skills, attributes and attitudes. Students at HL are required to study some topics in greater depth, in addition to the higher level material and in the common option. The distinction between SL and HL is one of breadth and depth. Core: Measurements and uncertainties; Mechanics; Thermal physics; Waves; Electricity and magnetism; Circular motion and gravitation; Atomic, nuclear and particle physics; Energy production. AHL: Wave phenomena; Fields; Electromagnetic induction; Quantum and nuclear physics. Option: Relativity or Imaging. Practical activities: 40 hours. Individual investigation: 10 hours. Group 4 project: 10 hours.",
                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future.",
                    "rules": { "pre": [["PHY010E130"]], "next": [["PHY112E150"]] }
                }, { "id": "PHY111E180",
                    "name": "A-Level Physics AS",
                    "track": "ASA2",
                    "level": "AS",
                    "description": "This course is designed to help students who intend to take the exams of A-Level Physics qualifications, including AS and A2 Level exams. Students can take the International AS Level qualifications in the end of grade 11. This course reward students\u2019 knowledge, understanding and application of a wide range of physics topics. Core contents in AS Level Physics cover themes including Mechanics, materials, waves, electricity, particles, nuclear physics and quantum physics. Oxford International AS Level Physics specification includes 5 required practicals. About 10% of the instructional time will be spent in hands-on laboratory work. Oxford International A-Level Physics provides a suitable foundation for the study of physics or related courses in higher education. It is equally suitable for candidates intending to pursue careers or further study in physics or engineering, or as part of a course of general education.",
                    "crowdRating": 6.7,
                    "crowdReview": "ISA - Hack the system. Build the future.",
