                    "level": "S",
                    "description": "This course is designed to teach students some of the major concepts and Laws of modern physics, with some historical context. The course of this year includes a study of wave, optics, quantum physics, atomic and nuclear physics, and digital technology. Students are required to spend 6 to 10 hours on practical work, including one project each semester. The course is expected to extend the students' understanding of Physics.",
