                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "H",
                    "description": "This one year course is designed for the students who have a curiosity about the physical world but do not expect to major in engineering or the physical sciences. Emphasis is placed on covering the phenomena, concepts, and theories of modern physics such as wave, optics, relativity, atomic and nuclear physics. Laboratory skills are developed. Students are expected to use scientific method to investigate, apply the ideas of physics to technology and develop an awareness of the impact of physics on society. Students are encouraged to take the SAT II in Physics upon completion of this course. At the same time, the course arranges related exercises on SAT II to help the student to attend the SAT II in Physics during the course.",
