                    "description": "This course is designed to help students who intend to take the exams of A-Level Physics qualifications, including AS and A2 Level exams. Students can take the International A2 Level Physics qualifications in grade 12. This course helps learners develop the knowledge and skills so that they will have a thorough understanding of key concepts in physics, an in-depth knowledge of the most important themes in physics and strong practical skills. The content of the A2 Level course covers a range of motion, rotation dynamics, gravitational fields, thermal physics, electronics and magnetism. Oxford International A2 Level Physics specification includes 10 required practicals. About 15% of the instructional time will be spent in hands-on laboratory work. Oxford International A-Level Physics provides a suitable foundation for the study of physics or related courses in higher education. It is equally suitable for candidates intending to pursue careers or further study in physics or engineering, or as part of a course of general education.",
